-- Chrysler Boosted Production 27% to Almost 2 Million in 2011
-- B y   C r a i g   T r u d e l l
-- 2012-01-11T22:14:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/chrysler-boosted-production-27-to-almost-2-million-in-2011.html
Chrysler Group LLC increased North
American production by 27 percent to almost 2 million vehicles
last year and plans a 20 percent boost for 2012.  The company’s output of cars and trucks in the U.S., Canada
and Mexico totaled 1.57 million in 2010, according to a
 statement  on the  Auburn Hills , Michigan-based automaker’s
website.  Chrysler’s assembly plants will ship 2.4 million vehicles
this year, Dan Knott, senior vice president of purchasing and
supplier quality, said today at the Automotive News World
Congress conference in Detroit.  Chrysler is majority owned by  Fiat SpA. (F)   Sergio Marchionne ,
chief executive officer of both automakers, plans to merge the
companies by the end of 2014 to achieve a target of more than
100 billion euros ($127 billion) in revenue.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Craig Trudell in Detroit at 
